OL,5, Men still earn more than women,        
OL,6, according to data gathered by the BBC. 
OL,8,FDespite a continued push for equality, 
OL,9,Fthe wage difference is still 9.4%, the 
OL,10,Fsame level as in 2017/18, when firms   
OL,11,Fwere forced to publish figures.        
OL,13,FThe figure is based on the difference  
OL,14,Fin pay between the middle-ranking woman
OL,15,Fand the middle-ranking man, the so     
OL,16,Fcalled median pay gap.                 
OL,18,FThis is different to unequal pay -     
OL,19,Fpaying women less for the same work -  
OL,20,Fwhich is illegal.                      
